      "writtenOn": "2016-12-01T19:56:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SGTM.\n\nThere are probably more efficient ways to go about it, but let\u0027s see how this does before getting more complicated. E.g. query for all PENDING, PENDING_RUNNING (whatever that means...), and RUNNING tasks without time restrictions; and also query for all COMPLETED tasks in the last 15 minutes. That would probably cover 95% of UnfinishedTasks().",
      "parentUuid": "2d6e6f0e_601adb89",
      "revId": "6cb3baff3a19b629c8cbdf4e2e925c7a14d20ad2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2d6e6f0e_764465b8",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 1192,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-01T20:34:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately, the time range is actually the creation time of the task, not the last-modified time, so we can\u0027t treat it like a \"changed since I last queried\" endpoint.",
      "parentUuid": "2d6e6f0e_93c2f323",
      "revId": "6cb3baff3a19b629c8cbdf4e2e925c7a14d20ad2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2d6e6f0e_d1d103e9",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 1192,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-01T21:45:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Understood. However:\nA. We want to know about all PENDING tasks, so we should query for all of them.\nB. We expect that most of the RUNNING tasks in these pools are generated by TS, so we should query for all of them.\nC. Many of our Build and Upload tasks (as well as some Test and Perf tasks) finish quickly, so querying the last 15 minutes for all tasks will probably give a pretty good hit rate for tasks in UnfinishedTasks(). The time required to query only the last 15 minutes should be ~6% of querying the last 4 hours.\nD. The \"remaining\" loop below would be used for tasks that ran longer than 15 minutes and have completed since the last time we queried. I would guess this is ~5% or less of UnfinishedTasks().\n\nIf querying all tasks in the last 4 hours works well, none of the above matters.",
      "parentUuid": "2d6e6f0e_764465b8",
      "revId": "6cb3baff3a19b629c8cbdf4e2e925c7a14d20ad2",
